<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880419-0185 </DOCNO><HL> Singapore's Trade Gap Widens </HL><SO> </SO><CO> FREST </CO><IN> MON </IN><DATELINE> SINGAPORE  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Singapore's trade deficit widened to 776.8 million Singapore dollars ($387.9 million) in March from 640.9 million dollars a year earlier and 475.2 million dollars in February.    March exports were 5.49 billion dollars, greater than the 4.19 billion dollars of a year earlier but less than the 5.9 billion dollars in February. Imports stood at 6.27 billion dollars in March, up from 4.83 billion dollars a year ago but smaller than the 6.38 billion dollars of the previous month. </TEXT></DOC>